name: integer_i16_one
description: |
  One is a baseline i16 operand for boundary arithmetic. Adding it to the
  maximum overflows, subtracting it from the minimum underflows, and dividing it
  by zero exercises integer divide-by-zero handling. These pairings also catch
  checks that are accidentally applied after an overflowing operation.
format: hex
decode-as: i16-le
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i16"
  - "one"
  - "overflow"
  - "underflow"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
01 00   # 1
